Taiwan June Energy Demand Falls 5.4% From Year Earlier, Coal Imports Slide

-- B y   Y u - H u a y   S u n
-- 
2011-08-08T01:39:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/taiwan-june-energy-demand-falls-5-4-from-year-earlier-coal-imports-slide.html
Taiwan’s June energy consumption fell
5.4 percent from a year earlier, the island’s energy bureau said
in an e-mailed statement today.   Coal imports dropped 19 percent to 5.17 million metric
tons, while imports of liquefied natural gas climbed 9 percent
to 1.38 billion cubic meters, the bureau said.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Yu-Huay Sun in Taipei at 
 ysun7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
